Phase 8 done — signed manifests. A p2present.json can carry an optional `sig` block proving who published it; the player verifies on load and shows a "✓ signed by <ENS/domain/0x…>" badge (subtle "unsigned" pill otherwise, "⚠ signature invalid" when present-but-bad) and NEVER blocks playback. Scheme: canonical JSON (p2/jcs-1, recursively sorted keys) of the whole manifest incl. sig.alg/signer/canon but excluding signature — so the signer claim is itself covered. Two algs: eip191 (Ethereum wallet personal_sign OR raw secp256k1 key; signer = recovered address, self-authenticating, ENS reverse-resolved read-only with forward-confirm + graceful fallback) and ed25519 (raw WebCrypto keypair; 32-byte pubkey + optional domain stored). Dependency-free pure-JS crypto: docs/src/crypto/{keccak,secp256k1,base64url,ens}.js (vector-checked: keccak empty/abc, privkey=1 + web3 key address, Node-interop recover) + docs/src/sign.js (canonicalize, sign/verify, describeSigner). Builder: 🔏 Sign card (connect wallet / paste ETH key / generate Ed25519) embeds the sig into the export/Open-in-player/?src= output, with a live "edited since signing — re-sign" staleness warning. Player: main.js verifies manifest._raw, header badge in app/index.html + app.css; ENS upgrade gated by window.__P2_ENS. SPEC + schema (optional sig, alg enum, required fields) updated; manifest.js carries raw.sig. Tests: 35/35 app unit (keccak/secp vectors, canonicalize stability, eip191+ed25519 round trip, tamper of content AND signer claim, unsigned ok, schema accepts) + 23/23 Worker + 99/99 smoke (signed→badge, tampered→invalid still plays, unsigned pill, builder sign+stale) green @ 390/780/1280, 0 real console errors, assets 200, static-only, light deps. Deployed live (Pages 200; schema + sign.js serving). Live: https://ibeezhan.github.io/p2present/app/
